## 8. WEEKLY PRICING MODEL (ACTUARIAL BASIS)

```
Premium Structure:
┌─────────┬──────────┬──────────┬────────────────────┬───────────────────┐
│ Tier    │ Premium  │ Coverage │ Target Workers      │ Expected Loss     │
│         │ (₹/week) │ (₹/week) │                    │ Ratio             │
├─────────┼──────────┼──────────┼────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
│ LOW     │ ₹15      │ ₹1,000   │ Low-risk zones,    │ 45-55%            │
│         │          │          │ non-monsoon         │                   │
├─────────┼──────────┼──────────┼────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
│ MEDIUM  │ ₹30      │ ₹2,500   │ Moderate zones,    │ 55-65%            │
│         │          │          │ seasonal risk       │                   │
├─────────┼──────────┼──────────┼────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
│ HIGH    │ ₹50      │ ₹5,000   │ High-risk zones,   │ 60-70%            │
│         │          │          │ monsoon season      │                   │
└─────────┴──────────┴──────────┴────────────────────┴───────────────────┘

Constraint: Premium ≤ 5% of worker's weekly earnings
  Worker earning ₹600/day × ~6 working days = ₹3,600/week
  Max premium = ₹180/week (well above our ₹50 cap)

Payout Scaling by DSI:
  DSI 65-80: 50% of coverage amount
  DSI 80-90: 75% of coverage amount  
  DSI >90:   100% of coverage amount

Shield Pool Discount:
  Pool of 5-10 workers:  -15% premium
  Pool of 11-25 workers: -18% premium
  Pool of 26+ workers:   -20% premium

Unit Economics (per 1000 workers/week):
  Revenue: 1000 × ₹30 (avg) = ₹30,000/week
  Expected Claims: 8% trigger rate × 1000 × ₹300 (avg payout) = ₹24,000
  Loss Ratio: 80% target (inclusive of operational costs)
  Break-even: ~500 insured workers at ₹30 avg premium
```

